
To configure network interfaces from the command line with nmcli:
https://people.freedesktop.org/~lkundrak/nm-docs/nmcli-examples.html

nmcli con add con-name "static-ens32" ifname ens32 type ethernet ip4 xxx.xxx.120.44/24 gw4 xxx.xxx.120.1

nmcli con mod "static-ens32" ipv4.dns "xxx.xxx.120.1,8.8.8.8"

nmcli con up "static-ens32" iface ens32

nmcli con del "old-name"



To configure WiFi:

https://nullr0ute.com/2016/09/connect-to-a-wireless-network-using-command-line-nmcli/

nmcli device wifi rescan
nmcli device wifi list
nmcli device wifi connect ${SSID} password ${PSK}
nmcli connection

